{title: Long Lines}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]This is a very long line of lyrics that goes on and on and on without stopping because sometimes songwriters write really long lines that extend well beyond what would normally fit on a single line of a typical song sheet and the renderer needs to handle wrapping gracefully
[C]Another extremely long line follows right behind the first one, continuing with even more words than before, stretching across the page like a river flowing endlessly through the countryside on a warm summer afternoon
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[Am]Short line for contrast
[Em]This line is moderately long but nothing compared to the earlier ones that stretched on for what seemed like forever and ever
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[F]The chorus also has a long line that tests how the renderer handles text wrapping in chorus sections which might have different formatting rules than regular verse sections depending on the configuration
[C]Short [G]end
{end_of_chorus}
